     Chancellor of the Exchequer George Osborne yesterday pledged a “fundamental reassessment” of state spending to tame a deficit that soared to 11 percent of gross domestic product in the year through March. Coulton speaks with Andrea Catherwood on Bloomberg Television's "The Pulse." (Source: Bloomberg)  
                           

     
